01:49:57,526 --> 01:50:00,086
Abe, meet my sister.

752
01:50:00,296 --> 01:50:02,127
I'm very happy to meet you.

753
01:50:02,331 --> 01:50:04,800
That's my dad.
Would you hold this for me?

754
01:50:05,902 --> 01:50:06,869
One second.

755
01:50:07,070 --> 01:50:10,267
I hoped you could recommend
a good school for journalism.

756
01:50:10,474 --> 01:50:13,444
I told my daughter I'd be
seeing you today.

757
01:50:13,644 --> 01:50:16,511
Just one minute, okay?
I'll be right back.

758
01:50:25,657 --> 01:50:29,457
Could I have your autograph?
I'm a great admirer of yours.

759
01:50:32,065 --> 01:50:34,761
Congratulations on your award,
it was well-deserved.

760
01:50:34,968 --> 01:50:38,233
Very impressive.
I was hoping you'd burst into song.

761
01:50:39,707 --> 01:50:42,437
- What are you doing here?
- You know what bothers me?

762
01:50:42,643 --> 01:50:43,473
What?

763
01:50:43,878 --> 01:50:46,574
It bothers me that you let Pran
stay in Cambodia...

764
01:50:46,780 --> 01:50:49,909
...because you wanted to win,
and you knew you needed him...

765
01:50:50,118 --> 01:50:52,848
- I didn't have any idea what...
- The fuck you didn't!

766
01:50:54,756 --> 01:50:56,883
The fuck you didn't.

767
01:50:57,492 --> 01:51:00,985
I did everything I could,
and I'm doing everything I can.

768
01:51:01,197 --> 01:51:03,529
Nice to see you.
I'm on my way to Florida.

769
01:51:03,733 --> 01:51:05,291
I'm doing everything I can.

770
01:51:05,501 --> 01:51:08,801
I'm sure. I didn't realize
you'd been out there to see him.

771
01:51:09,006 --> 01:51:12,271
Don't play games with me, Al.
Don't play stupid games.

772
01:51:12,476 --> 01:51:16,140
Nobody gets to go in there.
If I thought I could, I would.

773
01:51:17,015 --> 01:51:19,040
I've sent out hundreds of photographs.

774
01:51:19,250 --> 01:51:22,913
Every relief organization
on the Thai-Kampuchean border...

775
01:51:26,625 --> 01:51:30,425
...has got his picture. If I saw
one glimmer of hope, I'd go today.

776
01:51:30,963 --> 01:51:32,487
Life isn't a '40s movie.

777
01:51:32,698 --> 01:51:36,533
You can't just get on a plane and
make the whole world come out right!

778
01:51:38,138 --> 01:51:40,936
And I can't believe
I'm hearing this from you!

779
01:51:45,746 --> 01:51:47,043
Congrats.

780
01:51:49,116 --> 01:51:51,676
Do you keep in touch
with Dith Pran's family?

781
01:51:51,886 --> 01:51:54,082
Yes. They're living in San Francisco.

782
01:51:54,289 --> 01:51:57,156
How do you respond to accusations
that journalists...

783
01:51:57,359 --> 01:51:59,725
...underestimated the brutality
of the Khmer Rouge...

784
01:51:59,928 --> 01:52:03,660
...and so share responsibility for
what happened in Cambodia afterwards?

785
01:52:04,334 --> 01:52:06,165
We made a mistake.

786
01:52:06,736 --> 01:52:09,330
Maybe we underestimated
the kind of insanity...

787
01:52:09,539 --> 01:52:12,065
...that $ 7 billion worth
of bombing could produce.

788
01:52:12,276 --> 01:52:13,436
That is provocative...

789
01:52:13,644 --> 01:52:17,045
There have been a lot of refugee
stories in Reader's Digest...

790
01:52:17,248 --> 01:52:19,682
...about Cambodia.
Do you believe them?

791
01:52:19,883 --> 01:52:21,442
Don't you believe them?

792
01:52:21,653 --> 01:52:25,521
Maybe in this instance the
Reader's Digest happens to be correct.

793
01:52:25,724 --> 01:52:28,022
Do you apply the same disbelief
to stories...

794
01:52:28,226 --> 01:52:30,718
...that come out of Iran
or Palestine or Chile?

795
01:52:30,930 --> 01:52:33,296
Are refugees your next area
of interest?

796
01:52:33,499 --> 01:52:35,933
Will you be covering the boat people?

797
01:52:36,135 --> 01:52:37,261
No, I will not.

798
01:52:37,470 --> 01:52:39,166
Do you want a cup of tea?

799
01:52:40,140 --> 01:52:43,735
Are you looking around for some kind
of more salable suffering?

800
01:52:46,313 --> 01:52:48,942
I must have sent 500 letters.

801
01:52:54,455 --> 01:52:58,187
I wrote the International Red Cross,
the World Health Organization.

802
01:52:58,394 --> 01:53:01,090
I know you did, Syd.
You told me.

803
01:53:01,597 --> 01:53:03,861
I don't know who I didn't write to.

804
01:53:10,340 --> 01:53:13,002
I never really gave him any choice.

805
01:53:18,449 --> 01:53:21,577
One time we tried to discuss leaving.

806
01:53:30,529 --> 01:53:33,988
I talked to him about it,
but we never really discussed it.

807
01:53:37,303 --> 01:53:40,602
I discussed it with Swain and Rockoff.

808
01:53:44,611 --> 01:53:47,136
But I never discussed it with him.

809
01:53:58,326 --> 01:54:01,262
He stayed because
I wanted him to stay.

810
01:54:07,303 --> 01:54:09,168
And I stayed because...

811
01:57:48,615 --> 01:57:50,481
I'm trapped, Sydney.

812
01:57:50,684 --> 01:57:54,882
I know he suspects me,
and yet he treats me well.

813
01:57:55,522 --> 01:57:58,923
There are many different groups
over here, Sydney.

814
01:57:59,226 --> 01:58:01,320
I must take much care.

815
01:58:01,863 --> 01:58:05,924
Now Angka says we have new enemies.

816
01:58:06,468 --> 01:58:11,372
They say we must regain
our old lands from the Vietnamese.

817
01:58:12,141 --> 01:58:16,043
And now they say we must fight them.

818
01:58:17,848 --> 01:58:22,046
I miss you, my wife, my children.

819
01:58:22,252 --> 01:58:25,710
And my heart hungers for news of you.

820
01:58:49,849 --> 01:58:51,373
New China Radio reports...

821
01:58:51,584 --> 01:58:54,884
...that fighting between Vietnam
and Democratic Kampuchea...

822
01:58:55,089 --> 01:58:57,455
...has broken out
on a number of fronts.

823
01:58:57,725 --> 01:59:00,455
This is in retaliation,
according to the Vietnamese...

824
01:59:00,661 --> 01:59:03,095
...for a number of attacks
on border villages...

825
01:59:06,835 --> 01:59:08,200
Taxi driver, huh?

826
01:59:26,056 --> 01:59:27,887
I think you speak English.

827
01:59:28,358 --> 01:59:29,655
Sit down.

828
01:59:35,867 --> 01:59:38,392
You know, I love this country.

829
01:59:40,205 --> 01:59:43,004
I sacrificed everything for it.

830
01:59:44,477 --> 01:59:47,969
My wife died for the revolution.

831
01:59:49,883 --> 01:59:54,582
But the leaders of Angka
no longer trust the people.

832
01:59:55,522 --> 01:59:59,084
Therefore, I can no longer trust them.

833
02:00:00,928 --> 02:00:02,987
And they don't trust me.

834
02:00:05,500 --> 02:00:06,364
I fear...

835
02:00:07,769 --> 02:00:10,102
...really fear for the future.

836
02:00:14,510 --> 02:00:18,003
I think you love my son.

837
02:00:21,117 --> 02:00:22,379
For his sake...

838
02:00:23,453 --> 02:00:24,852
...look after him.

839
02:00:29,493 --> 02:00:32,087
The fighting is close by, Sydney.

840
02:00:32,296 --> 02:00:34,764
If the Vietnamese get here...

841
02:00:34,965 --> 02:00:37,127
...Angka will destroy everything...

842
02:00:39,271 --> 02:00:40,829
...and the Vietnamese,
they will find only ashes.

843
02:03:50,182 --> 02:03:53,618
I must try to stop the killing.
Good luck.

844
02:13:13,039 --> 02:13:14,939
Yeah, I'll be right there, Brian.

845
02:13:17,878 --> 02:13:21,837
Ann, get me 415-555-6421.

846
02:13:22,049 --> 02:13:23,744
Abe, I've got some great news!

847
02:13:36,966 --> 02:13:40,026
Twenty minutes ago, I get
a phone call from Paris.

848
02:13:40,236 --> 02:13:43,137
I get Andreas Freund.
He talked to Henry.

849
02:13:43,339 --> 02:13:45,433
He told him how to get in touch
with me.

850
02:13:45,642 --> 02:13:48,509
Freund says, "I have got
some great news for you."

851
02:13:48,712 --> 02:13:51,340
- San Francisco's on the line.
- "It's about Pran!"

852
02:13:51,715 --> 02:13:53,411
Is your mother there?

853
02:13:56,020 --> 02:13:57,180
When?

854
02:13:59,590 --> 02:14:02,253
All right,
I want you to get this down.

855
02:14:03,095 --> 02:14:05,757
No, write it down. Write it down.

856
02:14:07,299 --> 02:14:09,426
I've got a message from your dad!

857
02:15:22,382 --> 02:15:23,576
How you been?

858
02:15:36,665 --> 02:15:37,689
Do you forgive me?

859
02:15:38,400 --> 02:15:40,994
Nothing to forgive, Sydney.
Nothing.

